<span id="vi.iv.xiii.i-p3"></span><span class="c9"><span
id="vi.iv.xiii.i-p3.1"></span>Therefore</span> on the third day in
Tripolis, <span id="fr_1119"></span>[1120](#fn_1119.md) Peter rose early
and went into the garden, where there was a great water-reservoir, into
which a full stream of water constantly flowed.  There having bathed,
and then having prayed, he sat down; and perceiving us sitting around
and eagerly observing him, as wishing to hear something from him, he
said:—

